31/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Newly appointed KFOR Commander Lieutenant General Holger Kammerhoff paid a one-day visit to Skopje on Thursday (30 October), where he met with Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski. 
The two expressed satisfaction with the security situation in the area and vowed to continue exchanges of information and intensify bilateral co-operation in an effort to improve border control. 
They also expressed concerns with the extremist groups operating on the both sides of the border between Macedonia and Kosovo. 
(Utrniski Vesnik - 31/10/03; MIA, A1 TV - 30/10/03)
